  <text>
    <body>
      <div subtype="original" type="letter" xml:id="L.3263" xml:lang="en">
        <pb facs="#IMG.1" n="1"/>
        <opener>Dear Professor Schuchardt,</opener>
        <p>why so long silent? I burn for your criticisms and answers to some of my recent questions. M<hi rendition="#sup">r</hi>
          <persName
            ref="https://gams.uni-graz.at/o:hsa.persons#P.5342">E. Chatelain</persName> says that they will not accept any work for the <ref
            target="https://gams.uni-graz.at/o:hsa.subjects#S.5047">Ecole des Hautes Etudes</ref> because <ref
            target="https://gams.uni-graz.at/o:hsa.languages#L.837">Basque</ref> is not taught there! How foolish! why then don’t they teach it by making me professor or by publishing my Concordance which teaches it? My shepherd says that if he wrote darozkudazu it was a mistake as they write and say darozkidazu at his village. <persName
            ref="https://gams.uni-graz.at/o:hsa.persons#P.1466">Van Eys</persName> says that a Dutch Comparative Philologist named <persName
            ref="https://gams.uni-graz.at/o:hsa.persons#P.2898">Uhlenbeck</persName> is joining Hannemanns Basque Society – you should do so too. If anyone would publish my Concordance to Timothy I would with your leave dedicate it to you. Do you agree with <persName
            ref="https://gams.uni-graz.at/o:hsa.persons#P.1046">De Jubainville</persName> in unBasqueing the Ligurians? I notice that in his writings he almost ignores the Basques, probably because he is ignorant of Basque. I should like to see an etymological Basque Dictionary by you. I am revising for Thomas his copy of the first 29 chapters of D’Urtes Genesis. He thinks the Clarendon Press will print it. Priebsch goes to Oxford next week I believe. You would find Capanaga most useful if you coud only persuade that wretch <persName ref="https://gams.uni-graz.at/o:hsa.persons#P.1054">Arzac</persName> to publish it as he promised. Will you not revisit Basqueland next summer?</p>
        <closer>
          <salute>I remain yours truly</salute>
          <signed>
            <persName ref="https://gams.uni-graz.at/o:hsa.persons#P.1402">E. S. Dodgson</persName>. </signed>
          <dateline>18 Feb: 1893. 12 Rue de la Sorbonn, Paris.</dateline>
        </closer>
        <pb facs="#IMG.2" n="2"/>
      </div>
    </body>
